author: Sihan Goi
text: Trained here from 7-9am, the crowd was very manageable. It's quite a big branch with 4 half racks, a power rack, a platform, 1 hybrid bar per rack/platform, 1 set of Hammer Strength bumpers, and 1 extra pair of Ziva 15kg/20kg bumpers each. There are also ample black rubberized plates. Dumbbells up to 50kg, ample benches, plate loaded machines, cable machines, cardio machines, and a C2 rower. Also a hex bar and a short bar. In other words, quite well equipped. Half the bars don't spin very well though, but are good enough for general gym lifts though. Facilities wise, the bathroom is unisex, has 3 shower stalls and and toilet stall. Not sure about the service as it was pretty much unstaffed when I was there.

author: Venkata Vishnu
text:
I‚Äôve been really impressed with the Anytime Fitness at Northshore Plaza. The gym is spacious, modern, and very well-maintained, which makes every workout session comfortable. The equipment variety is excellent ‚Äî from free weights and strength machines to cardio and functional training gear, everything I‚Äôve needed has been available and in good condition. I was pleasantly surprised to see even a heavy bag, which adds great variety for boxing or conditioning workouts.

The staff are friendly, approachable, and always ready to help, which creates a welcoming vibe. The facility itself is kept clean and bright, with private showers and restrooms that are convenient after a workout. I also like that the gym is open 24/7, so I can fit in a session anytime, even with a busy schedule.

Highly recommend for anyone looking for a serious, supportive place to work out.

Overall, I highly recommend AF Northshore for anyone looking for a comfortable and enjoyable environment. I look forward to my next visit!

text:
Large gym located in Northshore Plaza.

Conditions of the equipments are pretty bad. Metal parts are either rusting, or needing to be oiled. Some equipments falling apart / too loose. Cables are loose for lat pulldown machine and rear delt machine. Aircon is leaking at many places (e.g. above barbell hip thrust, tricep extension machines).
Only 1 toilet for sharing, condition is worse than public mall toilets. Smell like pee and sometimes missing toilet paper. Water cooler is right outside the toilet cubicle...

The staff are genuinely friendly and helpful, which really adds to the experience. As for the new manager, a little smile wouldn‚Äôt hurt! üòÖ

All in all, it‚Äôs a solid gym with great value for money and a good atmosphere for serious workouts.

author: Mike Thye
text: I‚Äôm an active Northshore AF member since opening (2021) for 4 years. It always a best workout place for me. The staff and the previous manager(Siti) are friendly and professional. Siti always have a chat with us and listen to our feedback and maintain a very good relationship with us until the new manager took over the roles. The new manager never had a chat, or a greet, or not even an eye contact every time I entered the gym. I feel unwelcome to the gym. And with the recent incident, the class always been cancelled due to low participation. I understand about the policy on the min 4pax participation for the class to go on. But she even called for early cancellation for the class at 4pm+ while the cut off time is 6pm. And she claimed that she checked with regular attendees and no one can make it. The truth is most regular attendees are not being asked(already clarified). She misused her power just to cancel the class. Really disappointed with her management and decided to terminate the membership today due to the unpleasant experience.

text:
Anytime Fitness Northshore

author: Seah Astin
text:
Initially, I signed up a membership in Anytime Fitness Northshore because I wanted to conduct rehabilitation exercises on my knees. As I had been through an ACL knee surgery back then, I needed a place suitable to build up my knee strength again. That‚Äôs when I found out that AF Northshore was the place for me to work in.

They had all the relevant machines for me, such as the seated hamstring curl machine and the leg press machine to regain overall leg strength. After some time and consistent effort, I manage to recover from my ACL surgery, thanks to the service of AF Northshore.

Recovering from ACL surgery was part of the joyful experience in AF Northshore. I was made lots of new relationships with members and staffs of the gym. They were really friendly and kind towards me. The staff were willingly to answer all my queries. The members were nice enough to share machines with me, which made my workouts very soothing and enjoyable. Over time, the staff would bring in new machines for members to workout in, which I personally think they know what members are looking forward to!

author: Fuzzygg Gab
text:
I want to acknowledge upfront that this facility is one of the biggest in the area and the equipment is modern and well-maintained. However, the recent change in management has completely eroded the customer experience.

My issues are primarily threefold:

1. Condescending and Dishonest Management: The new manager has been consistently condescending in interactions. Furthermore, their dishonesty is unacceptable. They cancelled a class early, claiming "lack of participation," despite a clear demand from regular attendees. Our group chat confirmed this was a lie. Treating customers as if we are stupid is a sure way to lose our trust and business.
2. Threats Instead of Solutions: Instead of addressing concerns, the management's response to feedback has been to threaten us. We were explicitly told that classes with "not good attendance" will be shut down. This punitive approach, rather than working to improve scheduling or promotion, shows a complete disregard for member satisfaction.
3. Hypocritical Policies: This heavy-handed approach to class attendance is ironic, given their inflexibility with memberships. They would certainly not pause a subscription for a valid reason like a two-month overseas trip, despite being quick to cancel services we pay for.

Conclusion & Advice: My strong advice is to sign up elsewhere, especially if group classes are important to you. Fitness First or BFT are far better options for a reliable class schedule. Even other Active Fitness locations, like Punggol Oasis, have maintained their class standards. This location, however, under its current management, is not worth your time or money.

author: Crystal Yeo
text:
I'm the member since they opened at Northshore. I feel disappointed recently as they have cancelled the class (Tues - Jump Rope, Fri - Kickboxing, Sat - Muay Thai) i been attended for years due to low participants. My subscription fees has been increased from $80 to now $100 per month. However, no reduce at my subscription fees. There is a lot female member signed for the class instead of the machines/equipment. The class should go on even only two participants, this is unfair to the member. If you can't provide the class I might as well go to other gym center (eg: EnergyOne or 24/7) Also for those female member who just want to attend class can choice fitness center like TrueFitness, FitnessFirst or F45.

Besides, the manager is rude and reckless. She always calling while she is walking. Even bumped into me when I was doing chest training, no apologize at all. This is red flags in the gym. It may cause accident if member doing chest press.

Overall, I'm disappointed with this AF Northshore. Pls have a deep consideration if you're planned to sign on. Other than physical health, mentally health need to be taken care as well.

author: S N
text:
Air conditioned spacious gym being wasted with equipment placement not well planned. Every time I use the booty builder, the person using the rack in front of me or using the machine behind me can see me in an embarrassing position during my reps through the mirror reflection. Also, having the two  4-stack cable machine in the middle of the room will just make the place crowded and inconvenient to walk through. Dumbbells are mis-placed and not organized by weight. I think they only have 1 pair of 1.25kg plates regardless they have a really good Hammer strength side raise machine.

The staffs should definitely try out the gym by themselves. Their office is behind walls and I often see them inside chatting in groups and not caring about the gym.

The bathroom and shower are all unisex which is not acceptable for me as a female.

They have night classes every weekday 8pm and I have to give up using the functional area if I arrive late after work.
But I still love the location which is just beside the north shore view and could bicycle/jog home after workout.

text:

The staff here are super friendly and always up for a quick chat or happy to help if you need anything. The members are just as welcoming too  it really feels like a community where everyone supports each other, no matter where you are in your fitness journey.

The gym is clean, well-equipped, and has everything you need for a solid workout. Plus, there‚Äôs a really nice energy in the space that makes you want to keep coming back.

If you‚Äôre looking for a gym that‚Äôs spacious, friendly, and feels like a positive place to be, Anytime Fitness Northshore is definitely worth checking out!

author: Dannica Low
text:
Worst branch ever, with horrible staff service and the only branch that is all out to suck consumers' $$.

Charge $20++ admin fee for freezing membership with legit reason. Charge $15++ admin fee (failed payment fee) when card payment failed due to lost card, and associated it to their 3rd party merchandise Ezypay, even though I immediately engaged them to solve the payment issue and offered to make the payment asap on the same billing day, still insisted on charging me the admin fee (2 months in a row).

Spoke on the phone with a staff and he mentioned that admin fee cannot be waived because once Ezypay fails to transact the card payment, it is considered late payment even though i can still pay through other methods on the same billing day (not late yet). Staff explained because Ezypay will deduct anytime of the day from 00:00 onwards and once failed = late payment. This is obviously a coding logic flaw from their vendor and they are putting it on us consumers. Wow. Just wow. Please go review the processes, thanks.

Also, this fee is not written clearly in any of the clauses in the agreement. 0 leniency to discuss and waive fees. Just out to suck as much money from consumers. Ridiculously high "admin fee" of more than 15% for failure of card payment, and more than 20% admin fee for requesting to freeze membership.

Checked with my friends visiting other AF outlets, they never ever get charged additional fees for the above similar incidents... nicely asked if the fees could be waived and there was 0 leniency where the staff only repeated the same thing that didnt make sense and insisted on me paying.

Please be careful signing with this outlet. Whatever money they can earn from you, they wont let go and wont barge. Anyway, their toilet cubicle is always dirty and smelly, sometimes no toilet paper. Water cooler water very warm, most of the time is room temperature, not sure if is filtered... I have very good experiences with all other AF outlets, except Northshore.

author: Zetty MOHAMED
text:
I took package of  24 sessions. Paid $1920 & $95 for Membership. I'm not rich ya. Every single time my PT Clarence kept rescheduling. Imagine the 2nd session, already started asking me to reschedule. The 4th time he ask me to reschedule when I'm on the way there by grab. I told him no. I'm on the way. Really pissed off. My motivation of workouts vanish. Imagine arh signed up for 24 sessions. As a single parent managing my life, work and supporting my sick mum. I decided to cancel my membership but since I knew that I signed for 18 months contract, I can't cancel. Fine! I understand that. Siti the manager from Northshore Plaza told me why I can't give the new PT a chance. PT Andrew not to bad but incident happen when my first session with him, he stretch my back until I can't walk the next day. I highlighted that I got lower back issue, my tennis elbow and asthmatic. In fact, all the PT knew of my health condition. We should inform them. They should know right our condition.
Took me many months to forget the incident. Then came a message from PT Sap! He texted me twice but the gap wasn't that close. I decided to go for the lesson with him. So far I like the way he conduct the lesson. No much stress. He also knew where my strength & weakness. He told me he found I don't sweat & with some exercises while working out, that make me sweat! Tired but enjoying. Well done PT Sap!
Another new issue started, only this month April, I cant pay due to my business slow. Receive 3 reminders to pay for my outstanding. Just my first time. Even the government or mobile company etc don't send multiple of reminders in a month. Really like tailong. Big companies like AF keep sending multiples reminders?
They asked me to pay April & one month notice. Meaning two months? Already can't afford to pay two months since I told them. I want to cancel. I don't remember the staff told me after the 18 months contract, I still have to give one month notice.
And now I told them about my current conditions, asking for their email address so that my FSC counsellor and explain to them for leciency, but they ignore my WhatsApp message for several days. Time is ticking. They expect me to pay by 30 April but they ignore my message for several days. Simple ask for Email address for my counsellor to explain my current situation. My anxiety. Now I left with today and tomorrow. How to get my counsellor to email them when tomorrow is the last day to cancel? Are they playing games so that i have to pay 2 + 1 month fees?
All they want me they wanna talk to me on the phones while I'm now not in good conditions. Down with flu, cough, asthma attacks due to their reminders make me sick. A simple question, the higher management email so that my counsellor can ask for leniency. If HDB and other government can, why can't they? Even the subcourt also does have leniency to us.
Only today they give me the email address. 30/4?? They seriously playing games with me. Since 24/4, I have been asking. Tomorrow new month. Tomorrow my counsellor don't work. 30/4, I got appointment with my counsellor.
All I can say AF only think for packages $$$$ never ask us check with us since they knew that PT Clarence loves to reschedule their clients. they can't give any leniency for me? They only send reminders because of late payment but they don't bother to check with members who have sign up with PT,  check about their PT... Monthly subscription $95 cos I am having v v tight budget, they can't deduct the membership. Have to pay extra. Other Co late payment also no that much. Theirs more than $30.
Due to this, I can't work. My anxiety, makes my health really down. No work no money. We freelancer... Last week already sick and again I can't work yesterday after receiving their message that they want me to pay by 8/5. I got shop/studio rental to pay by 7/5 the latest.
